<% provide(:title, "Home") %>

<section>
  <h3>Instructions:</h3>
  <p>Select a patient population based on cancer diagnosis, chemotherapy start or other factors that you'd like
    included in this analysis, and an episode length (generally 1-12 months). For that population, pull all diagnosis
    codes, procedures, treatment plans and ED/IP encounter dates. All data fields are prepopulated with national average
    data based on the SEER sample. If you're missing any data points, the SEER data will be used as a default.</p>
  <p>Alternatively, you can prepare and upload Excel files containing your patient level data. These files will not be
    uploaded to the COME HOME database and we will process as much as possible on your servers. However, this
    application is not currently housed in on a HIPAA compliant server, so please do not include any PHI.</p>

</section>
<section>
  <h2>Step 1: Patient information</h2>
  <div>
      <button name="Upload a demographic file">Upload a demographic file</button>
      <br>
      <br>
      <div>
        <label>Number of Patients per Month: </label><input type="number" id="npts" name="npts" value="100">
        <label>% Female: </label><input type="number" id="ndx" name="ndx" value="50">
        <label>Number Age 0-18: </label><input type="number" id="nchild" name="nchild" value = "0">
        <label>Number Age 9-25: </label><input type="number" id="nya" name="nya" value ="10">
        <label>Number Age 26-64: </label><input type="number" id="nadult" name="nadult" value = "40">
        <label>Number Age 65-79: </label><input type="number" id="nelderly" name="nelderly" value = "30">
        <label>Number Age 80+: </label><input type="number" id="nextelderly" name="nextelderly" value = "20">
      </div>
  </div>

</section>
<section>
  <h2>Step 2: Cancer Dx</h2>
  <div>
    <button name="Upload a dx file">Upload a diagnosis file</button>
    <br>
    <br>
    <label>Number of New Breast Cancer Diagnoses: </label><input type="number" id="nnewbreast" name="nnewbreast" value="25">
    <label>% Metastatic: </label><input type="number" id="nrecbreast" name="nrecbreast" value="5">
    <label>% ER/PR Positive: </label><input type="number" id="nrecbreast" name="nrecbreast">
    <label>% Her2 Positive: </label><input type="number" id="nrecbreast" name="nrecbreast">
    <label>Number of New Colon Cancer Diagnoses: </label><input type="number" id="nnewcolon" name="nnewcolon" value="25">
    <label>% Metastatic: </label><input type="number" id="nreccolon" name="nreccolon" value="5">
    <label>% KRAS Positive: </label><input type="number" id="nnewlung" name="nnewlung">
    <label>Number of New Lung Cancer Diagnoses: </label><input type="number" id="nreclung" name="nreclung" value="25">
    <label>% Metastatic: </label><input type="number" id="nreccolon" name="nreccolon" value="5">
    <label>% ALK Positive: </label><input type="number" id="nreccolon" name="nreccolon">
    <label>% EGFR Positive: </label><input type="number" id="nreccolon" name="nreccolon">
    <label>Number of New Other Cancer Diagnoses: </label><input type="number" id="nnewother" name="nnewother" value="25">
    <label>% Metastatic: </label><input type="number" id="nrecother" name="nrecother" value="5">
  </div>
</section>
<section>
  <h2>Step 3: Comorbidities</h2>
  <div>
    <label>% of Patients with Diabetes: </label><input type="number" id="ndx" name="ndx" value="5">
    <label>% of Patients with Coronary Artery Disease: </label><input type = "text" value="5">
    <label>% of Patients with Congestive Heart Failure: </label><input type="text" value="5">
    <label>% of Patients with Mild Liver Disease: </label><input type="text" value="5">
    <label>% of Patients with Moderate to Severe Liver Disease: </label><input type="text" value="5">
    <label>% of Patients with HIV: </label><input type="text" value="5">
    <label>% of Patients with ESRD: </label><input type="text" value="5">
  </div>
</section>
<section>
  <h2>Step 4: Potentially Avoidable Complications</h2>
  <div>
    <label>Which Diagnosis Codes should be considered Potentially Avoidable Complications?<br><br><br><br><br></label>
    <input type="checkbox" name="pacdx" value="No"> None<br>
    <input type="checkbox" name="pacdx" value="dvtpe"> DVT/PE (453.xx, 415.1x - 415.2)<br>
    <input type="checkbox" name="pacdx" value="sepsis"> Sepsis (955.91, 955.92)<br>
    <input type="checkbox" name="pacdx" value="pneu"> Pneumonia (486.xx)<br>
    <input type="checkbox" name="pacdx" value="Other"> <input type="text" name="otherpac"> Separate other ICD9 codes with commas<br>
    <label>% of Patients with DVT/PE: </label><input type="number" id="ndx" name="ndx" value="5">
    <label>% of Patients with Sepsis: </label><input type = "text" value="5">
    <label>% of Patients with Pneumonia: </label><input type="text" value="5">
  </div>
</section>
<section>
  <h2>Step 5: Utilization</h2>
  <div>
    <button name="Upload a proc file">Upload a utilization file</button>
    <br>
    <br>
    <label>Average Number of Office Visits Per Month: </label><input type="number" id="ndx" name="ndx">
    <label>% of Patients with ER Visit Per Month: </label><input type = "text">
    <label>Average ER Visit Cost: </label><input type="text">
    <label>% of Patients with IP Admission Per Month: </label><input type="text">
    <label>Average IP Cost Per Admission: </label><input type="text">
    <label>% of Patients receiving PET Scans: </label><input type="text">
  </div>
</section>
<section>
  <h2>Step 6: Treatment</h2>
  <div>
    <button name="Upload a proc file">Upload a treatment file</button>
    <br>
    <br>
    <label>Average number of chemotherapy hours per week: </label><input type="number" id="ndx" name="ndx">
    <label>% of patients receiving chemo per month: </label><input type="text">
    <label>% of patients receiving Neulasta: </label><input type = "text">
    <label>% of patients receiving monoclonal antibodies: </label><input type="text">
    <label>% of on oral chemotherapy: </label><input type="text">
  </div>
</section>
<section>
  <h2>Step 7: Payment Model</h2>
  <div id="pm">
    <label>What is the trigger for a new episode in the proposed model?<br><br><br></label>
    <input type="radio" name="trigger" value="FirstVisit"> First Visit<br>
    <input type="radio" name="trigger" value="NewDx"> New Diagnosis<br>
    <input type="radio" name="trigger" value="ChemoStart"> Chemotherapy/Hormone Therapy Start<br>
    <input type="radio" name="trigger" value="NoTrigger"> None (for models that don't use episodes of care)<br>
    <input type="radio" name="trigger" value="Other"> Other
    <br>
    <br>

    <label>How long does an episode last? If the model does not use episodes of care enter 0 (zero).</label>
   <input type="number" name="length"> months
    <br>
    <br>
    <br>
    <label>Will you receive a stipend to cover infrastructure or other costs?<br><br><br><br></label>
    <input type="radio" name="pmpmyn" value="ssunlimited"><input type="number" name="pmpmyn" value="500"> One Time<br><br>
    <input type="radio" name="pmpmyn" value="ssunlimited"><input type="number" name="pmpmyn" value="50"> Per Member Per Month (PMPM)<br><br>
    <input type="radio" name="pmpmyn" value="No"> No<br>
    <input type="radio" name="pmpmyn" value="Other"> Other
    <br>
    <br>
    <label>Will you receive a stipend to cover chemotherapy storage and handling?<br><br><br><br></label>
    <input type="radio" name="pmpmchemo" value="ssunlimited"><input type="number" name="pmpmyn" value="500"> One Time<br><br>
    <input type="radio" name="pmpmchemo" value="ssunlimited"><input type="number" name="pmpmyn" value="50"> Per Member Per Month (PMPM)<br><br>
    <input type="radio" name="pmpmchemo" value="No"> No<br>
    <input type="radio" name="pmpmchemo" value="Other"> Other
    <br>
    <br>
    <label>Will you be eligible for shared savings?<br><br><br><br></label>
    <input type="radio" name="sharedsavings" value="ssunlimited"> Yes, with no limit<br>
    <input type="radio" name="sharedsavings" value="ssdollarcap"><input type="number" name="sspercentcap">% cap<br><br>
    <input type="radio" name="sharedsavings" value="No"> No<br>
    <input type="radio" name="sharedsavings" value="Other"> Other
    <br>
    <br>
    <label>Will you accept downside risk?<br><br><br><br></label>
    <input type="radio" name="risk" value="ssunlimited"> Yes, with no limit<br>
    <input type="radio" name="risk" value="ssdollarcap"><input type="number" name="riskpercentcap">% cap<br><br>
    <input type="radio" name="risk" value="No"> No<br>
    <input type="radio" name="risk" value="Other"> Other
    <br>
    <br>
    <label>For practices accepting downside risk, will you purchase reinsurance?<br><br></label>
    <input type="checkbox" name="reinsurance" value="perpatient"> Per episode<br>
    <input type="checkbox" name="reinsurance" value="poplation"> Per population<br>
    <input type="checkbox" name="reinsurance" value="No"> None<br>
    <input type="checkbox" name="reinsurance" value="NA"> N/A
    <br>
    <br>
    <label>Which services will be included in the bundle (check all that apply)<br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br>
      <br><br><br><br></label>
    <input type="checkbox" name="bundleinclude" value="officevisit"> Office Visits<br>
    <input type="checkbox" name="bundleinclude" value="phone"> Phone Calls (physician phone consults, nursing
    triage calls, etc.)<br>
    <input type="checkbox" name="bundleinclude" value="labs"> Labs<br>
    <input type="checkbox" name="bundleinclude" value="imaging"> Diagnostic imaging<br>
    <input type="checkbox" name="bundleinclude" value="dxproc"> Other Diagnostic Procedures<br>
    <input type="checkbox" name="bundleinclude" value="chemo"> Chemotherapy Administration<br>
    <input type="checkbox" name="bundleinclude" value="chemodrugs"> Chemotherapy Drugs<br>
    <input type="checkbox" name="bundleinclude" value="hormone"> Hormone Therapy<br>
    <input type="checkbox" name="bundleinclude" value="rads"> Radiation Therapy<br>
    <input type="checkbox" name="bundleinclude" value="ed"> ED Encounters<br>
    <input type="checkbox" name="bundleinclude" value="ip"> IP Admissions<br>
    <input type="checkbox" name="bundleinclude" value="outside"> Other outside utilization<br>
    <input type="checkbox" name="bundleinclude" value="fu"> Follow up
    <br>
    <br>
    <label>Is the bundled payment reconciled prospectively or retrospectively?</label>
    <input type="radio" name="timing" value="Prospective"> Prospective (lump sum paid out directly after trigger
      event) <br>
    <input type="radio" name="timing" value="Retrospective"> Retrospective (practice paid via FFS with reconciliation
      and additional payments at end of episode)
    <br>
    <br>
  </div>
  <p><label>Bundled Payment Amount (if known): $</label><input type="number" name="bp" id="bp">
    <br>
    <br>
